orking people needed skills to succeed in the new economy moving people from welfare to work working with disadvantaged youth through the youth opportunity program history home page labor hall of honor indepth research annals of the department history esources departmental timeline historical office century of service wirtz labor library freedom of information act   privacy  security statement   disclaimers   important web site notices   plugins used by dol us department of labor  frances perkins building  constitution ave nw washington dc  wwwdolgov  telephone usadol   tty  contact us herman alexis m  toggle navigation prototype home about prototype herman alexis m  alternative names dates birth  gender maybe same as herman alexis authority source viaf worldcat nara lc lc nationality language eng latin alphabet biographical notes alexis margaret herman was born july   in mobile alabama a daughter of alex herman and gloria caponis she received a ba in sociology in  from xavier university of new orleans louisiana she married dr charles franklin after college she worked for catholic charities and other agencies advocating minority women employment in  she became director of the womens bureau of the department of labor serving until  in  she founded the consulting firm am herman  associates during her tenure as chief of staff and later vice chair of the democratic national committee herman was responsible for organizing the  democratic national convention following the election of president clinton she became deputy director of the presidential transition office she was later appointed assistant to the president and in  director of the white house office of public liaison herman served as secretary of labor from may   to january   during her tenure the priorities were a prepared workforce a secure workforce and quality workplaces she facilitated negotiations between united parcel service management and teamsters union leaders ending a tenday strike other major issues included retooling the departments skills programs into a simpler more efficient system giving working people needed skills to succeed in the new economy moving people from welfare to work and working with disadvantaged youth through the youth opportunity program from  to  independent counsel ralph i lancaster investigated allegations that she solicited illegal campaign contributions and engaged in influence peddling while she was white house public liaison following her government service he served the boards of several major companies including coca cola corporation toyota cummins metro goldwyn mayer and prudential from the description of herman alexis m  us national archives and records administration naid  biographical notes are generated from the bibliographic and archival source records supplied by data contributors links to collections archival collections  creator of referenced in berry faith papers of faith berry  bulk  library of congress berry faith papers  bulk  library of congress faith berry papers  bulk   manuscript division library of congress washington dc records of independent counsels    electronic records relating to alexis m herman related resources  futurework  trends and challenges for work in the st century  labor day   a report of the united states department of labor alexis m herman secretary creatorof labor day  creatorof measuring state and local government labor productivity creatorof measuring state and local government labor productivity  examples from eleven services creatorof report of the united states department of labor creatorof report on the youth labor force creatorof trends and challenges for work in the st century creatorof ww am politics  creatorof related external links  archivegrid search dpla search lc name authority file lc name authority file virtual international authority file worldcat identities herman alexis m  sameas related names in snac people  berry faith correspondedwith herman alexis maybesameas families  orga