ed or poorly sourced must be removed immediately especially if potentially libelous or harmful december  learn how and when to remove this template message alexis herman rd united states secretary of labor in office may   – january   president bill clinton preceded by robert reich succeeded by elaine chao director of the office of public liaison in office january   – february   president bill clinton preceded by cecile kremer succeeded by maria echaveste director of the womens bureau in office – president jimmy carter preceded by carmen rosa maymi succeeded by lenora cole alexander personal details born alexis margaret herman  july   age  mobile alabama us political party democratic spouses charles franklin education edgewood college spring hill college xavier university louisiana ba alexis margaret herman born july   is an american politician who served as the rd us secretary of labor serving under president bill clinton prior to her appointment she was assistant to the president and director of the white house office of public engagement contents  early life and education  career  see also  references  external links early life and educationedit herman was born on july   in mobile alabama the daughter of politician alex herman and schoolteacher gloria caponis she grew up in a catholic home in mobile and earned her high school diploma in  from the heart of mary high school she briefly attended edgewood college in madison wisconsin and spring hill college in mobile but transferred to xavier university of louisiana in new orleans where she became an active member of the gamma alpha chapter of delta sigma theta sorority and graduated with a bachelor of arts in sociology in  herman was queen of carnival for the mobile area mardi gras association mobiles africanamerican mardi gras umbrella organization in  her carnival king douglas wicks would go on to become the first africanamerican elected to the mobile county commission since reconstruction careeredit after college herman worked for catholic charities and other agencies advocating for minority women employment jimmy carter met the young herman while campaigning in atlanta georgia and after winning the white house in  asked her to be director of the labor departments womens bureau at age  she was the youngest person to ever serve in that position hermans official us department of labor portrait in  herman founded her own consulting firm  am herman  associates she served as president of the company while remaining active in democratic politics during her tenure as chief of staff and later vice chair of the democratic national committee she was responsible for organizing the  democratic national convention after bill clintons victory in the  presidential election herman became deputy director of the presidential transition office she was later appointed to head the white house office of public liaison where she was responsible for the administrations relations with interest groups during clintons second term herman was named secretary of labor the first african american to be nominated for that position and the fifth woman to be appointed her nomination was initially opposed by congressional republicans and labor unions but she earned praise from her peers for her handling of the  ups workers strike herman came under investigation for allegedly accepting kickbacks while working at the white house she was the th cabinet officer be investigated by independent counsel in  the independent counsel concluded that herman had broken no laws and cleared her of all wrongdoing she was also mentioned in connection with the commerce department trade mission controversy during the  florida election recount herman was part of team planning a transition to a gore administration and she was mentioned as a likely candidate for white house chief of staff she was replaced as secretary of labor in the george w bush administration by elaine chao herman now serves as the cochairperson with james roosevelt jr of the democratic national committees rules and bylaws committee herman also now serves on the boards of several major companies including the cocacola companys human resources task force toyotas diversity advisory board cummins mgm resorts international entergy sodexo and prudential and is the chairman and ceo of new ventures inccitation needed see alsoedit list of africanamerican united states cabinet secretaries referencesedit  alexis herman bio from kevocom  notable deltas delta sigma theta sorority inc archived from the original on january    retrieved december    wwwmamgacom wwwmamgacom retrieved    women in government a slim past but a strong future ebony – – august    nytimescom april   labor secretary is cleared in inquiry on kickbacks by neil a lewis   whos who on the rules and bylaws committee nprorg retrieved    mydd vote counting the dnc rules  bylaws committee archived  at the wayback machine  cnncom its decision day for democrats archived may   at the wayback machine external linksedit us department of labor biography private attorney chosen to investigate alexis herman cnn allpolitics may   clinton questioned in alexis herman investigation cnn september   congressional record—senate s april   labor secretary is cleared in inquiry on kickbacks ny times april   jonathan karl on the possible sleeper case in the election dispute cnn december   political offices preceded by cecile kremer director of the office of public liaison – succeeded by maria echaveste preceded by robert reich united states secretary of labor – succeeded by elaine chao v t e assistant to the president for public liaison special counsel to the president special assistant to the president assistant to the president for public liaison assistant to the president for public outreach assistant to the president for public engagement and intergovernmental affairs charles colson william j baroody jr midge costanza anne wexler elizabeth dole faith whittlesey linda chavez mari maseng rebecca range bobbie kilberg cecile b kremer alexis herman maria echaveste minyon moore mary beth cahill lezlee westine rhonda keenum julie e cram valerie jarrett george sifakis v t e united states secretaries of labor secretaries of commerce and labor cortelyou metcalf straus nagel secretaries of labor wilson davis doak perkins schwellenbach tobin durkin mitchell goldberg wirtz shultz hodgson brennan dunlop usery marshall donovan brock mclaughlin dole martin reich herman chao solis perez acosta v t e cabinet of president bill clinton – cabinet secretary of state warren m christopher – madeleine albright – secretary of the treasury lloyd bentsen – robert rubin – larry summers – secretary of defense les aspin – william j perry – william s cohen – attorney general janet reno – secretary of the interior bruce babbitt – secretary of agriculture mike espy – dan glickman – secretary of commerce ron brown – mickey kantor – william m daley – norman mineta – secretary of labor robert reich – alexis m herman – secretary of health and human services donna shalala – secretary of housing and urban development henry g cisneros – andrew m cuomo – secretary of transportation federico peña – rodney slater – secretary of energy hazel oleary – federico peña – bill richardson – secretary of education richard w riley – secretary of veterans affairs jesse brown – togo west –  acting secretary cabinetlevel vice president al gore – white house chief of staff mack mclarty – leon panetta – erskine bowles – john podesta – administrator of the environmental protection agency carol m browner – ambassador to the united nations madeleine albright – bill richardson – richard c holbrooke – director of the office of management and budget leon panetta – alice rivlin – franklin d raines – jack lew – director of national drug control policy lee p brown – barry mccaffrey – trade representative mickey kantor – charlene barshefsky – director of the federal emergency management agency james l witt – director of central intelligence r james woolsey jr – john m deutch – george tenet – chairperson of the council of economic advisers laura tyson – joseph stiglitz – janet yellen – martin neil baily – administrator of the small business administration philip lader – aída m álverez –  took office in  raised to cabinetrank in  authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn n isni     gnd  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlealexishermanoldid categories clinton administration cabinet members birthsafricanamerican members of the cabinet of the united statesafricanamerican women in politicsalabama democratsthcentury american politiciansdelta sigma theta membersdirectors of the cocacola companyliving peoplepeople from mobile alabamaspring hill college alumniunited states secretaries of laborwomen in alabama politicswomen members of the cabinet of the united statesxavier university of louisiana alumnihidden categories webarchive template wayback linksblp articles lacking sources from december all blp articles lacking sourcesall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from june wikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with lccn identifierswikipedia articles with isni identifierswikipedia articles with gnd identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other projects wikimedia commons languages العربيةdeutschespañolفارسیfrançaisitalianoעבריתpolskisimple englishsuomi edit links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative